body_html:
@YoWhatever I'm guessing the root cause information comes just above the lines in the 2nd picture you provided. You can save the entire log to a text file with adb logcat | tee log.txt, and then just upload log.txt after you've captured an instance of it crashing.

What is odd to me is that you only have 7 nodes in your graph. Are the input and output nodes named the same? Possibly you're trying to use an operator that isn't supported on mobile?

body:
@YoWhatever I'm guessing the root cause information comes just above the lines in the 2nd picture you provided. You can save the entire log to a text file with `adb logcat | tee log.txt`, and then just upload log.txt after you've captured an instance of it crashing.

What is odd to me is that you only have 7 nodes in your graph. Are the input and output nodes named the same? Possibly you're trying to use an operator that isn't supported on mobile?
